jobs_results.title: iOS Mobile Developer
jobs_results.description:
iOS Mobile Developer

Our client is an award winning, regulated, global financial services company, providing customers with multi-asset and multi-market trading capability through financial spread betting products, leveraged Forex trading and CFD trading. They are experiencing significant growth in their retail customer base across a number of countries, and need motivated people to help them expand.

As the iOS Mobile Developer, you will be a key part of the team responsible for the onward development of the customer and trading platform on iOS mobile and tablet apps. You will create new functionality and maintain existing components.

You are someone with 3-5 years‚Äô experience in a similar role that genuinely enjoys developing apps to improve customer experience, and has a keen interest in expanding and developing your knowledge through working in a fast-paced trading company.

Responsibilities include:

¬∑ Manage and lead the development of the trading platform iPhone and iPad apps taking responsibility for both individual and team deliverables.

¬∑ Work with your team to develop the platform iPhone and iPad apps to meet the expectations of our customer.

¬∑ Keep abreast of the latest mobile techniques and technologies, advise the business of the benefits and implement where appropriate.

¬∑ In this hands-on role you will also be carrying out design and development activities.

¬∑ Working closely with the Testing team to resolve issues that arise during the testing of developed software.

¬∑ Working closely with the mobile product owner to ensure that user stories are appropriately documented and understood as part of the agile, scrum based development lifecycle

¬∑ Working with the company‚Äôs Support team to resolve problems with the trading platforms and associated technology.

This is not intended to be an exhaustive or exclusive list of duties. You may be required to carry out any other associated tasks to ensure the successful delivery of the company‚Äôs objectives.

Skills and experience:

Essential

¬∑ Excellent experience of developing for the iOS platform.

¬∑ Good experience of developing using native Objective-C and Cocoa touch within the Xcode IDE.

¬∑ Strong awareness of timelines and task priority.

¬∑ Good communication skills are required, with the ability to understand and communicate issues succinctly and without ambiguity using appropriate technical vocabulary.

¬∑ Fluent in English.

¬∑ Experience of working within a team.

¬∑ Right to work in the Cyprus

Preferred

¬∑ Knowledge of HTML, CSS and JavaScript would be a distinct advantage.

¬∑ Experience of Android app development would be a distinct advantage.

Please forward your CV/Application to info@skao.com.cy or call us on 22774424 for more details on how to apply.

jobs_results.title: Mobile Application Developer  (VAC-A20202G)
jobs_results.description:
Our client is an established FX company based in Limassol and they are looking to recruit a mid to senior level Mobile Application Developer to join our Engineering team. You will be working with our engineers to develop and maintain high quality mobile applications.

What you'll do:

Develop new user-facing interfaces for mobile applications.

Build reusable code and libraries.

Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs.

Optimize mobile applications for maximum speed and scalability.

Assure that all user input is validated before submitting to the back-end.

Collaborate with other team members and stakeholders.

Maintain code and write automated tests to ensure the product is of the highest quality.

What you have:

2+ years of experience working with Swift and Java/Kotlin,

4+ years of professional software development experience, working experience in mobile development,

An understanding of React Native/Flutter best practices and a commitment to following them,

Demonstrable portfolio of released applications on the App store or the Android market,

BSc degree in Computer Science or relevant field,

Meaningful experience working on large, complex systems,

Experience with third-party libraries and APIs,

Be proficient in using version control and continuous integration, with tools such as Git and Jenkins,

What You Can Expect:

An attractive remuneration package from 3000 -4000 Euros based on candidate's experience and qualifications;

A high tech and collaborative international working environment;

Performance recognition/bonus;

Corporate Medical Insurance Scheme from the first day of employment;

Our client is an equal opportunity employer and we are committed to promote diversity and equality. The client takes care about the privacy of its candidates and all the data provided is maintained in a secure manner and kept confidential.

TO APPLY for this job opportunity, send your CV (in English please) to admin@smstaffmatters.com and include the reference: Mobile Application Developer - VAC-A20202G. We look forward to hearing from you!
